   288Рєњ/// The `Error` type, a wrapper around a dynamic error type.
   289Рєњ///
   290Рєњ/// `Error` works a lot like `Box<dyn std::error::Error>`, but with these
   291Рєњ/// differences:
   292Рєњ///
   293Рєњ/// - `Error` requires that the error is `Send`, `Sync`, and `'static`.
   294Рєњ/// - `Error` guarantees that a backtrace is available, even if the underlying
   295Рєњ///   error type does not provide one.
   296Рєњ/// - `Error` is represented as a narrow pointer &mdash; exactly one word in
   297Рєњ///   size instead of two.
   298Рєњ///
   299Рєњ/// <br>
   300Рєњ///
   301Рєњ/// # Display representations
   302Рєњ///
